Arma replication

Jim Savage

9 August 2016

This just tries to get the ARMA model running

First, lets make sure that Jeffs code runs

resid <- rnorm(200, 0, 1)
mu <- 0.02
theta <- -0.5

Y_diff <- NULL
for(i in 2:200) {
  Y_diff[i] <- mu + theta*resid[i-1] + resid[i]
}

plot.ts(Y_diff, main = "differenced Y")

# Now plot Y
plot.ts(cumsum(Y_diff[-1]), main = "log of Y")

Now that we have some data, lets fit Jeffs model to make sure that we can recapture the known parameters \(\theta = -0.5\), \(\mu = 0.02\) and \(\sigma = 2\).
